<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="11" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Shape somewhat variable, but maculation consistent in presence of white apical dash on the forewing which forms a connection with a white, swooping &quot;postmedial lunule&quot; which may or may not form a continuous white band outlining the postmedial line (
<bibRefCitation author="St Laurent, RA" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="76" pageNumber="77" pagination="31 - 116" title="Revision of the genus Menevia Schaus, 1928 (Lepidoptera, Mimallonoidea, Mimallonidae) with the description of 11 new species." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.566.6982" volume="566" year="2016">St Laurent and Dombroskie 2016</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="11" type="apomorphy">
<paragraph pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Apomorphy.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="10" pageNumber="11">(1) Paired, elongated, thin, tusk-like extensions reaching outwards from modified transtilla/juxtal complex which itself extends inward into the body cavity from attachments on either side of the inner costal apodemes of the valvae (Fig. 3a).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
